<p><b>James Mercer Langston Hughes</b>, (February 1, 1902 – May 22, 1967) was an American <a href="/wiki/Poet" title="Poet">poet</a>, <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novelist</a>, <a href="/wiki/Playwright" title="Playwright">playwright</a>, <a href="/wiki/Short_story" title="Short story">short story</a> writer, and <a href="/wiki/Columnist" title="Columnist">columnist</a>. Hughes is best-known for his work during the <a href="/wiki/Harlem_Renaissance" title="Harlem Renaissance">Harlem Renaissance</a>.</p>
